AB  - The purpose of this paper is to analyse and model the determinants of the supply of international financial services, on the basis of the recent available data. The empirical results of this study for 13 OECD countries, in a cross-sectional analysis, indicate that national R&D, banks' international assets and physical and human capital are among the factors which provide the competitive edge for the financial institutions of the developed countries to deliver effective and efficient international financial services.
