AB  - We reexamine the bidder stock price response to regulatory approval of 11 merger conversion transactions during 1983 to 1987. Bidding firms earn insignificant abnormal returns in the period preceding approval, but the regulatory approval announcement generates a significant negative price response. Our results are in contrast to those reported in Shilling (Journal of Banking and Finance, 15 (1991) 165–172).
